race.comment: TYPHOON BAYLEE (3) was well fancied last time and led throughout to score (25.70) at Geelong in a Grade 4/5 over 460m. Winner at his latest appearance in one of the quickest times on the card. Hard to fault his form and he makes plenty of appeal. DUSTY MCGRAW (1) is worth forgiving last start after finishing fourth (24.07) from Box 6 at Bendigo over 425m. Boasts a strong record from this draw with five wins and two minor placings from seven starts. Great chance to atone. PAW XENA (8) is better than last start when sixth (25.71) from Box 4 at this track over 450m. Goes very well from this draw with three wins and three minor placings from seven starts. Can do much better this time. LITTLE DARL (2) is worth another chance despite missing the top-three here most recently.
